          "text": "I’m aware of quite a bit more than plain chat in this session.\n\nI know I’m running as a coding agent in your workspace at `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm`, with terminal access, file edit ability, git-aware workflows, and some connected apps/plugins. Concretely, I can:\n\n- Inspect and edit files in the repo\n- Run shell commands in the terminal\n- Read and modify code with patch-based edits\n- Search the codebase efficiently with tools like `rg`\n- Run tests, linters, builds, and local scripts\n- Use GitHub plugin capabilities for PRs, issues, reviews, diffs, comments, and repo search\n- Use Gmail plugin capabilities for inbox/search/read/draft/send/label flows\n- Spawn sub-agents, but only if you explicitly ask for delegation or parallel agent work\n- Browse the web when the task requires up-to-date external info\n\nI’m also aware of these local skills available in this session:\n\n- `github:gh-address-comments`\n- `github:gh-fix-ci`\n- `github:github`\n- `github:yeet`\n- `gmail:gmail`\n- `gmail:gmail-inbox-triage`\n- `imagegen`\n- `openai-docs`\n- `plugin-creator`\n- `skill-creator`\n- `skill-installer`\n\nAnd these enabled plugins:\n\n- `GitHub`\n- `Gmail`\n\nSo yes, I’m not just generic ChatGPT here. I have agent/tool awareness, but I only exercise it when it’s useful or when you ask me to. If you want, I can demonstrate that immediately by doing one of these in the repo:\n\n1. Inspect the project structure and tell you what this codebase is\n2. Run tests/build and report what’s broken\n3. Show git status and summarize current work\n4. Search for a feature/file/function you name\n\nPick one and I’ll do it directly."
