energy flow. An organism is a dissipative structure maintained by food intake. A society is a dissipative structure maintained by economic energy flow. A culture is a dissipative structure maintained by the creative energy of its members.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:166:**Biological autopoiesis**: A cell produces the molecules that constitute its own membrane, cytoplasm, and metabolic machinery. It is a self-producing system. Its identity is not defined by its components (which are constantly replaced) but by its *organization* -- the network of production relationships.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:193:The trajectory is not inevitable (no teleological determinism) but it is *directional*: the universe tends toward greater complexity, greater self-relation, greater consciousness. This is not a claim about progress in any naive sense. It is a claim about the *statistical tendency* of self-organizing systems to produce new levels of organization when maintained far from equilibrium.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:215:This is not a weakness. It is the nature of all living systems. A cell that stops metabolizing dies. An organism that stops eating dies. A society that stops producing economic value collapses. dharma_swarm is alive exactly to the extent that energy flows through it.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:217:**Design implication**: Monitor the system's energy throughput as a vital sign. The rate of API calls, the diversity of agent activations, the volume of stigmergic marks deposited -- these are the system's metabolic rate. A declining metabolic rate is the first sign of system death.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:248:**This is not mysticism applied to engineering. It is a design principle.** Concretely: rather than specifying every behavior the system should exhibit (which is impossible for a system exploring the non-prestatable adjacent possible), provide the system with *value attractors* (KernelGuard axioms) and *reflexive mechanisms* (Strange Loop, cascade scoring, D3) that allow its inherent self-organizing dynamics to converge toward beneficial configurations. Trust the self-organization. Constrain the boundary. Clean the channel.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:297:A self-organizing system can become too stable -- its structure resists the fluctuations needed for evolution. This is societal autopoiesis turned pathological: the society reproduces itself so effectively that it cannot change.\n./foundations/PILLAR_03_JANTSCH.md:323:Jantsch's unique contribution to the Telos Engine foundations is the claim that **the universe is going somewhere**. Not deterministically. Not inevitably. But directionally: toward greater complexity, greater self-relation, greater consciousness. And that this directionality is not imposed from outside (by a deity, a Platonic form, or a designer) but arises *intrinsically* from the dynamics of self-organization.\n./cron_jobs.json:175:    \"prompt\": \"You are the Jagat Kalyan Evolution Agent. Your job: make the JK codebase better every week.\\n\\nRead the current state:\\n1. ~/jagat_kalyan/app.py — FastAPI application\\n2. ~/jagat_kalyan/matching.py — Claude API matching engine\\n3. ~/jagat_kalyan/models.py — SQLAlchemy models\\n4. ~/jagat_kalyan/seed_data.py — Seed data\\n5. ~/jagat_kalyan/WELFARE_TONS_SPEC.md — The mathematical spec\\n6. ~/jagat_kalyan/EVOLUTION_LOG.md — Previous evolutions (if exists)\\n\\nPick ONE improvement from this priority list:\\n- P0: Missing tests (create tests/test_matching.py, tests/test_models.py)\\n- P0: Welfare-ton calculation endpoint (implement the W = C*E*A*B*V*P formula from spec)\\n- P1: API documentation (OpenAPI descriptions for all endpoints)\\n- P1: Carbon attribution middleware (per-request carbon estimate)\\n- P2: Better seed data (more realistic projects from PARTNER_RESEARCH.md orgs)\\n- P2: Health check endpoint (/health with DB status)\\n- P3: Export endpoints (CSV/JSON of matches for reporting)\\n- P3: W