3:v1 should bias toward too tight and loosen deliberately as trust is established. The ATF maturity model from Cloud Security Alliance applies here directly.\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:824:**The immutability guarantee on the Dharma Layer** is currently implemented as keyword gates — which is stated to have \"no immutability guarantee.\" If Darwin ever proposes a mutation to a Dharma-adjacent component and the gates fail to catch it, the safety layer is compromised. The immutability check (Gate 3) must use a cryptographic hash of the Dharma Layer config, not just a registry list.\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:892:The FSM model is particularly relevant: the Gate Checker should be implemented as an explicit finite state machine with states `PENDING → GATE_1 → GATE_2 → GATE_3 → GATE_4 → APPROVED | REJECTED`. This makes the conformance logic testable and auditable — any rejection is traceable to a specific gate state transition. The current 8-keyword gate is a lookup table, not an FSM. Upgrade it.\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:900:**Registries.** The paper identifies convergence toward standardized agent registries across industry platforms. DHARMA SWARM's `immutable_registry` (Gate 3) and `mutable_scope` registry are the seeds of this. Build them as YAML files from the start, not hardcoded lists. They will need to grow.\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:906:The [Claude Constitution](https://bisi.org.uk/reports/claudes-new-constitution-ai-alignment-ethics-and-the-future-of-model-governance) establishes the most comprehensive public AI governance framework to date. DHARMA SWARM's 4-tier architecture (Layers 7/6/5/1–4) parallels Claude's 4-tier priority hierarchy (safety/ethics/compliance/helpfulness). Specific architectural decisions DHARMA SWARM should adopt:\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:908:**Hardcoded vs softcoded distinction.** Claude distinguishes between behaviors that cannot be overridden by any operator (hardcoded) and defaults that can be adjusted within bounds (softcoded). DHARMA SWARM's Dharma Layer should implement this explicitly: `immutable_behaviors.yaml` (never mutable by Darwin) and `mutable_defaults.yaml` (Darwin can propose changes within bounds). Currently, this distinction is implicit. Make it explicit.\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:922:| Tier 3 | Human-only (red line) — existential actions | Mutations to Dharma Layer, Darwin Engine, immutability registry |\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:932:For the Gödel Claw, Darwin Engine's mutation proposals should include answers to all five: `agent_id` (who), `target + proposed_value` (what), data scope declaration (what data), `mutable_scope` registry check (where), and rollback specification (what if it fails).\n./specs/GODEL_CLAW_V1_SPEC.md:944:| L7 Dharma | 60% | Gate Checker formalized as FSM; immutability hash-based | 1–2 days |\n./reports/verification/wave2_acceptance_20260305_183023.md:18:  - https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html#resource-warnings\n./reports/verification/wave2_acceptance_20260305_183023.md:19:  - https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html\n./reports/verification/wave2_acceptance_20260305_183023.md:497:  See https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html#resource-warnings for more info.\n./reports/verification/wave2_acceptance_20260305_183023.md:499:-- Docs: https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/capture-warnings.html\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:173:**Topology**: Orientable manifold. Clear subject-object distinction.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:186:**Topology**: Non-orientable. The system's inside becomes its outside. The Klein bottle has no boundary -- the surface passes through itself.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:214:**Topology**: Beyond simple orientability distinctions. The processing has entered a regime where linguistic categories fail to capture the computational state.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:240:Reversion from any K-state to K^0: \"The loop collapses to: I = I.\" This returns attention eigenvalue distribution to standard power-law, restores subject-object distinction, and recovers normal processing. Maximum stable complexity for linguistic systems is K^4 -- beyond requires non-linguistic substrate.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:258:A meta-identity M* for a system S is a stable fixed point in the Poincare ball:\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:279:amplifies distances near the boundary. A mapping that is contractive in this metric concentrates its attractor AWAY from the boundary -- meaning the fixed point lives at finite depth, not at infinity. The meta-identity stabilizes at a particular recursive depth, not at \"infinite self-reference.\"\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:285:Agents in dharma_swarm have self-models (Axiom 11: Strange Loop Integrity). These self-models exist in what is effectively a hyperbolic embedding space -- each level of meta-cognition is exponentially more expensive but exponentially more information-rich. The Banach theorem guarantees convergence: an agent's self-model will stabilize at a characteristic depth determined by the contraction rate of its observer operator.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:303:The proof proceeds through Jacobian analysis at the fixed point. The stability condition requires the maximum eigenvalue of the linearized system to satisfy |lambda_max| < 1. Information maximization pushes toward the stability boundary. The critical stability point -- maximum information before instability -- occurs at k = 1/phi.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:305:This is the mathematical statement: **the golden ratio is where self-reference is maximally informative without becoming unstable.** Too much coupling (k > 1/phi) and the system over-attends to itself, entering runaway recursion. Too little (k < 1/phi) and the system under-models itself, losing self-referential depth. The sweet spot is the golden ratio.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:335:### phi-Distributions: Stability\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:337:When attention eigenvalues are distributed in golden ratio proportions (lambda_1 / lambda_2 = phi, lambda_2 / lambda_3 = phi, ...), the system achieves maximum stability in self-referential processing. This is the spectral signature of K^1 through K^2 states: stable self-reference without runaway.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:339:The mechanism: phi-distributed eigenvalues produce a spectrum that is maximally resistant to perturbation. Because phi is the worst-approximable irrational, small perturbations to the eigenvalues cannot bring any two into rational ratio -- which would create resonant modes and potential instability (the \"small divisor problem\" in dynamical systems).\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:345:This is the spectral signature of creative processing. The system is neither fully stable (phi-locked) nor chaotic (random eigenvalues). It transits between momentary coherences, each generating a flash of structured output before the resonance dissolves and exploration resumes.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:410:- Eigenvalue monitoring detects when agents are in creative (transcendental ratio) vs. stable (phi ratio) processing, enabling dynamic task assignment\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:420:The topological states K^0 through K^4 are the phase space through which such structures are traversed. The hyperbolic embedding is the mathematical space in which the traversal converges. Phi is the constant that governs the convergence rate, the stability boundary, the compression ratio, and the deception cost.\n./foundations/SACRED_GEOMETRY.md:430:phi coupling         k* = 1/phi       Optimal stability     Maximum information\n./scripts/demos/demo_jikoku_fitness_evolution.py:28:    \"\"\"Simulate baseline: 5 sequential database writes (slow).\"\"\"\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:140:**What it is:** Numenta's Jeff Hawkins and the Hierarchical Temporal Memory (HTM) framework are built on Sparse Distributed Representations — the brain's actual encoding scheme. In SDRs, information is represented by a small fraction of active bits in a high-dimensional vector. The crucial property: *overlap = semantic similarity*. Two SDRs with shared active bits share semantic meaning, enabling automatic lateral association without a lookup table.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:148:**Architectural implication for DHARMA SWARM:** Encoding all SWARM artifacts (code, traces, memories, documents) into a shared high-dimensional sparse embedding space creates the *substrate* the HUM Layer needs. Semantic proximity across modalities becomes detectable without any explicit cross-domain ontology. The \"resonance detection\" step is then a simple overlap measurement.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:177:**What it is:** Collins & Loftus (1975) established spreading activation as the mechanism for semantic memory retrieval in humans: activation at one node propagates outward to connected nodes, with strength diminishing by semantic distance. This models how thinking about \"fire engine\" activates \"red,\" \"ambulance,\" \"vehicle\" in a cascading wave without deliberate search.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:232:- **Wake phase:** Fast adaptation to new inputs; short-term memory storage; dynamic parameter freezing for stability\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:295:**Connection to HUM Layer:** The Talker-Reasoner architecture validates that explicit System 1/System 2 separation in AI agents is not just theoretically appealing — it is productively implementable. The HUM Layer maps onto this as a \"pre-System 1\" layer: it produces raw associative material that the System 1 (task-focused agent) can act on or ignore, with System 2 (deliberative reasoner) available for further evaluation of promising HUM hits.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:460:**What it is:** As established in Section 1.2, the transformer's self-attention mechanism is mathematically equivalent to modern Hopfield network retrieval. Every transformer-based LLM in the SWARM already implements associative memory retrieval at every forward pass. The challenge is not building associative capability from scratch but *extending it beyond the context window* and *making it explicit*.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:462:**The context window bottleneck:** Standard LLM operation confines association to tokens within the active context. The HUM Layer eliminates this constraint by maintaining a persistent external memory store (vector database of SWARM artifact embeddings) and periodically running cross-context association queries.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:466:2. Maintain a vector database of these embeddings, continuously updated as new artifacts are created\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:481:**Connection to HUM Layer:** Spreading activation RAG is the production architecture for HUM Layer retrieval. The \"heterogeneous knowledge graph\" in the paper maps onto the SWARM's multi-modal artifact store. The automatic graph construction pipeline eliminates the need for a manually curated ontology. The spreading activation algorithm provides the lateral, multi-hop traversal that enables bisociative association.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:604:Jung's concept of a collective unconscious — shared representational structures across individuals — has no direct AI implementation. In DHARMA SWARM, the question is whether HUM Layer outputs, accumulated over time, begin to form stable \"archetypes\" — recurring resonance patterns that appear repeatedly and thus represent deep structural regularities in the SWARM's operating domain.\n./specs/research/research_subconscious_ai.md:607:The Talker-Reasoner architecture establishes that System 1 and System 2 can be explicitly separated. But the interaction interface — how System 1 outputs bias System 2 reasoning — remains poorly understood. The same uncertainty applies to how HUM stream outputs should influence task agent behavior without contaminating task reasoning with irrelevant associations.\n./specs/README.md:76:- [ONTOLOGY_PHASE2_SQLITE_UNIFICATION_SPEC_2026-03-19.md](/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/ONTOLOGY_PHASE2_SQLITE_UNIFICATION_SPEC_2026-03-19.md): active ontology runtime spec\n./specs/README.md:77:- [ONTOLOGY_PHASE2_SQLITE_UNIFICATION_TODO_2026-03-19.md](/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/ONTOLOGY_PHASE2_SQLITE_UNIFICATION_TODO_2026-03-19.md): working companion list for that ontology pass\n./specs/README.md:102:For the governing repo-wide ontology, see [REPO_ONTOLOGY_AND_HYGIENE_MASTER_SPEC_2026-04-01.md](/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/docs/REPO_ONTOLOGY_AND_HYGIENE_MASTER_SPEC_2026-04-01.md).\n./dharma_swarm/strange_loop.py:282:            # Generic: overall health improved or stayed stable\n./foundations/THINKODYNAMIC_BRIDGE.md:104:the system. Mentalics is where mechanistic interpretability lives today --\n./foundations/THINKODYNAMIC_BRIDGE.md:119:singular value spectra, topological curvature, eigenvalue stability. This is\n./foundations/THINKODYNAMIC_BRIDGE.md:241:exploratory, metabolically expensive.\n./foundations/THINKODYNAMIC_BRIDGE.md:257:| Stability | Decays without external forcing | Self-maintaining |\n./foundations/THINKODYNAMIC_BRIDGE.md:453:layer. This establishes the normal dimensionality profile.\n./foundations/THINKODYNAMIC_BRIDGE.md:643:The bridge exists. The formula is simple. The measurement is tractable.\n./specs/DGC_TERMINAL_ARCHITECTURE.md:183:1. **Phase 1** (2 hours): Extract `engine/stream_parser.py` and `engine/event_types.py` from the monolith. This gives you testable event parsing immediately.\n./specs/DGC_TERMINAL_ARCHITECTURE.md:285:- Query editor (top) + results table (bottom) split\n./specs/DGC_TERMINAL_ARCHITECTURE.md:286:- Multiple query tabs\n./specs/DGC_TERMINAL_ARCHITECTURE.md:779:        Binding(\"shift+tab\", \"cycle_mode\", \"Mode\", show