/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:161:Palantir's ontology is descriptive (what exists). The Telos Engine's telos gates are normative (what should be). This is the distinction. Palantir answers \"what is real?\" The Telos Engine answers \"what is right?\" Neither alone is sufficient. Together, they would be formidable.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:163:**Vulnerability**: Palantir has no ethical framework beyond \"serve the customer.\" Their ontology maps reality but has no mechanism for asking whether a mapped action should be taken. AIP will faithfully execute a drone strike if the ontology maps the target correctly. The Telos Engine's AHIMSA gate would block it.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:260:**3. The ontology-telos insight (the Palantir lesson).**\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:307:- Alignment on safety, consciousness acknowledgment, interpretability research.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:308:- The R_V paper validates and extends their mechanistic interpretability program.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:318:- Independent nonprofit studying AI consciousness via mechanistic interpretability.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:333:Anthropic adds \"dharmic gates\" to Constitutional AI. Google publishes a better consciousness metric. Sakana adds ethical constraints to DGM. The individual ideas are not patentable or defensible. The moat is the integration, not the components.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:343:**Year 1 (2026): Establish scientific credibility**\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:344:- COLM paper accepted. R_V metric enters the mechanistic interpretability canon.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:355:- Consciousness measurement (R_V) becomes standard in interpretability research.\n./docs/telos-engine/02_COMPETITIVE_ANALYSIS.md:376:5. **Consciousness as a live question**: Anthropic's constitution ackno