dation Model Transparency Index 2025). Carbon offset markets meant to address this are broken: 90%+ of REDD+ credits are phantom (Guardian/Die Zeit investigation). Meanwhile, Anthropic's own researchers (Massenkoff & McCrory, March 2026) project that 300 million jobs are in the blast radius of AI automation, with hiring rates for 22-25 year-olds in high-exposure positions already measurably slowing. GAIA solves all three problems -- energy accountability, verified offsets, displaced-worker livelihoods -- through a single integrated system. The cost to build and prove the MVP is $3-6 million. That is less than a single large training run. The cost of inaction is regulatory surprise, reputational exposure, and ceding the standard to a competitor.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:155:Massenkoff and McCrory (\"Labor Market Impacts of AI,\" Anthropic, March 2026) established an early-warning system for AI-driven displacement:\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:168:| McKinsey | 30% of US jobs automatable; 60% undergo significant changes | By 2030 |\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:171:The WEF has published a direct warning about the **\"overlooked global risk of the AI precariat\"** -- workers displaced into unstable, lower-quality employment rather than outright unemployment. In the first two months of 2026, 32,000 tech jobs were cut. In 2025, approximately 55,000 cuts were directly attributed to AI out of 1.17 million total layoffs.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:189:GAIA (Grounded AI for Integrated Accountability) is a platform connecting AI companies' measured compute footprints to verified ecological restoration projects staffed by displaced workers, with algebraic conservation laws preventing fraud.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:218:Why not blockchain? Compositionality (complex transactions decompose into verifiable morphisms), type safety (the system literally cannot mix units), formal verification (conservation laws are machine-checkable), and auditability (any claim traceable to raw data) -- all without the energy cost and complexity of distributed consensus.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:227:| IoT Sensor | Soil carbon, water table, temperature | Ground-truth continuous monitoring |\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:238:- **`gaia_ledger.py`** (682 lines): Five categorical objects, five typed morphisms, five conservation laws enforced algebraically, BLAKE2b hash-chained append-only commitment log with full auditability. `ConservationLawChecker.check_all()` runs every conservation law on every transaction.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:250:**Mission alignment.** Anthropic's stated mission is building AI that is safe and beneficial. GAIA makes \"beneficial\" concrete and measurable: X tons CO2 sequestered, Y workers employed at Z wages, verified by independent oracles. \"Beneficial AI\" becomes an auditable claim rather than a marketing statement.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:276:- Public, auditable dashboard showing the complete chain from compute energy to verified carbon sequestration to worker paychecks\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:287:The MVP proves one thing: that the loop from AI compute measurement through ecological restoration through independent verification to public accountability can be closed, with real workers doing real restoration work and real data showing real results. Everything else can be built on that foundation.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:373:If Google builds this first -- and Google has the emissions data, the satellite infrastructure via Google Earth, and the financial resources -- Anthropic will be using Google's environmental accountability framework. That is a dependency no AI safety company should accept.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:383:The MVP costs $3-6M and takes 12 months. It produces a publicly auditable pipeline from Anthropic's compute energy to verified carbon sequestration to worker paychecks. It gives Anthropic environmental reporting infrastructure before the EU AI Act requires it, closes the Stanford Transparency Index gap, and creates a coherent ethical position that unifies model welfare with environmental accountability.\n./docs/dse/GAIA_ANTHROPIC_MEMO.md:385:The question is not whether AI companies will be held accountable for their ecological footprint. The question is whether Anthropic sets the standard or follows someone else's.\n./dashboard/src/app/dashboard/agents/page.tsx:5: * Data table with agent list, inline HP bars, status dots.\n./dashboard/src/app/dashboard/agents/page.tsx:74:            <table className=\"w-full text-left text-sm\">\n./dashboard/src/app/dashboard/agents/page.tsx:151:            </table>\n./dharma_swarm/contracts/common.py:4:implementation so that adapter layers can map existing stores into stable\n./docs/dse/gaia_pilot_feedback_sample.json:15:    \"summary\": \"Evidence paths are auditable and the monitoring snapshots preserve uncertainty instead of flattening it.\",\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:2:title: Runtime Stabilization Implementation Plan\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:3:path: docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:4:slug: runtime-stabilization-implementation-plan\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:12:  - docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:56:  vault_path: docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:61:  - stabilization\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:79:      access_mark: Opening, linking, and revising docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md reinforces its salience without needing a separate message.\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:95:# Runtime Stabilization Implementation Plan\n./docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md:110:- Modify: `docs/plans/2026-03-28-runtime-stabilization.md`